<header id="detail-header">
	<h1>The Jazz Singer</h1>
</header>

	<section id="film-detail-container">
		<img src="../static/images/m03.jpeg" alt="Film poster">

		<p><em>The Jazz Singer</em> is a musical drama film directed by Alan Crosland, starring Al Jolson, May McAvoy, Warner Oland, and Yossele Rosenblatt.</p>

		<p>Darryl F. Zanuck produced the film.</p>

		<p>
			It was released by Warner Bros. Pictures on October 27, 1927, with a runtime of 89 minutes.

			
				It had a budget of $422,000  and made $2.6 million at the box office.
				When adjusted for inflation in 2023, that's approximately equivalent to $7.2 million and $45 million, respectively.
			
		</p>

		<p>
			The film was written by Alfred A. Cohn, with Louis Silvers composing the filmâ€™s music. Hal Mohr oversaw cinematography, and Harold McCord helped with editing the film.
		</p>

		<p><a href="https://archive.org/details/the-jazz-singer-1927">View an archived version of <em>The Jazz Singer</em>.</a></p>

		<p><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Jazz_Singer">View the Wikipedia entry for <em>The Jazz Singer</em>.</a></p>

		<p><a href="../index.html">Return to the list</a> to select a different film.</p>
	</section>

